City of Chicago, Plaintiff in Error, v. Charles A. Selleck, Defendant in Error.Gen. No. 20,007.

(Not to be reported in full.)

Error to the Municipal Court of Chicago; the Hon. David Sullivan, Judge, presiding. Heard in the Branch Appellate Court at the April term, 1914.Affirmed.Opinion filed January 26, 1915.

Statement of the Case.

This case was consolidated for hearing with the case of City of Chicago v. Allen, reported on p. 189 ante, and the decision in that case held controlling in this.

William H. Sexton and James S. McInerney, for plaintiff in error; Albert J. W. Appell, of counsel.Francis E. Croarkin, for defendant in error; Francis W. Walker, of counsel. Mr. Presiding Justice Barnes

delivered the opinion of the court.
